50|$|In the U.S. {{a partial}} {{amortization}} or <b>balloon</b> <b>loan</b> {{is one where}} the amount of monthly payments due are calculated (amortized) over a certain term, but the outstanding balance on the principal is due at some point short of that term. In the UK, a partial repayment mortgage is quite common, especially where the original mortgage was investment-backed.|$|E
